## Prerequisites

- Android SDK (API {{ target_sdk | default(34) }}+)
- QAIRT SDK installed (`source activate.sh`)
- Java 8 (`export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64`)

## Setup

```bash
# 1. Copy SNPE AAR to libs/
mkdir -p app/libs
cp $QAIRT_SDK_ROOT/lib/android/snpe-release.aar app/libs/

# 2. Copy model to assets
mkdir -p app/src/main/assets
cp {{ model_path }} app/src/main/assets/

# 3. Set environment
export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-openjdk-amd64
export ANDROID_SDK_ROOT=<path-to-android-sdk>
```

## Build

```bash
./gradlew assembleDebug
```

Output APK: `app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk`

## Install & Run

```bash
adb install -r app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk
adb shell am start -n {{ package_name | default('com.qualcomm.quad.inference') }}/.MainActivity
```

## Usage in Code

```kotlin
val engine = SNPEInferenceEngine(application)

// Load model (supports File or FileInputStream)
engine.loadModel(File("/sdcard/model.dlc"))

// Run inference
val inputData = FloatArray(3 * 224 * 224) { /* preprocessed image */ }
val results = engine.execute(inputData)

// Get top-5 predictions
val topK = engine.getTopK(results.values.first(), k = 5)
topK.forEach { (classId, score) ->
    Log.i("QUAD", "Class $classId: ${"%.4f".format(score)}")
}

// Cleanup
engine.release()
```

## Runtime Selection

The `loadModel()` method accepts a runtime fallback order:

| Runtime | Flag | Description |
|---------|------|-------------|
| DSP | `Runtime.DSP` | Hexagon DSP (8-bit fixed point) |
| GPU | `Runtime.GPU` | Adreno GPU (float16/float32) |
| AIP | `Runtime.AIP_FIXED8_TF` | HTA+HVX (8-bit) |
| CPU | `Runtime.CPU` | Snapdragon CPU (float32) |

Default order: `DSP → GPU → CPU` (falls back if unavailable).

